## Objective
Build a complete gridcalc-xl spreadsheet engine library according to SPEC.md, implementing all requirements (R1-R28) and passing all tests.

## Important Details
- **SPEC.md location**: `/Users/arden/code/ornith-loopspace-experiments/gridcalc-xl/runs/solo/SPEC.md`
- **Package structure**: `gridcalc/` with modules: `__init__.py`, `ast.py`, `evaluator.py`, `lexer.py`, `parser.py`, `sheet.py`, `workbook.py`
- **Public API**: Single `Workbook` class with sheets exposing `set(addr, raw)`, `get(addr)`, and `eval_count` property
- **Key constraints**: No floats, no deletion APIs, no file I/O, no UI, pure-logic library
- **Test command**: `pytest -q` from repo root
- **Status**: 61 tests written, many failing due to parser/evaluator bugs

## Work State
### Completed
- Added missing `evaluate()` function to `evaluator.py` (entry point for Sheet.get())
- Fixed `sheet.py set()` to accept empty string literals (R2 compliance)
- Rewrote `parser.py` to handle IDENT tokens containing both column and row (e.g., "A1")
- Fixed `_get_cell()` and `_get_cell_keyed()` to use `sheet._cells` instead of `sheet.cells`
- Created comprehensive test suite `test_gridcalc.py` with 61 tests covering G1-G10 acceptance groups

### Active
- Fixing parser issues: unary minus stacking, ranges in function args, qualified refs, function calls with multiple args
- Fixing evaluator: cache not working (eval_count increases on repeat reads), error ordering wrong (#TYPE! before #DIV!), cycle detection not working
- Fixing sheet: `define_name()` validation (NAME syntax is uppercase only), `copy()` doesn't accept qualified src
- Fixing workbook: undo/redo not restoring cell content properly, eval_count handling

### Blocked
- Parser fails on: `=-=1`, `=SUM(A1:A2)`, `=CONCAT("a","b","c")`, `=IF(1,10,20)`, `=NOW()`, `=S1!A1`
- Evaluator returns wrong errors: `=A01+1` returns #TYPE! instead of #REF!, `=1/0+1` returns #TYPE! instead of #DIV!
- Cycle detection not working: `=A2+1` with A2=`=1/0` returns #TYPE! instead of #CYCLE!
- Undo/redo doesn't restore cell content properly

## Next Move
1. Fix parser to handle all function calls (SUM, MIN, MAX, COUNT, CONCAT, LEN, IF, NOW) with proper argument parsing
2. Fix parser to handle qualified references (SHEET!REF) and range arguments
3. Fix evaluator cache to prevent eval_count from increasing on repeat reads
4. Fix error ordering to follow left-to-right precedence (R5)
5. Fix cycle detection to work correctly (R9)
6. Run `pytest -q` and iterate until all tests pass

## Relevant Files
- `/Users/arden/code/ornith-loopspace-experiments/gridcalc-xl/runs/solo/SPEC.md` - Full specification (do not modify)
